  "prompt": "Does every student at iiser get fellowship?",
  "response": "At the Indian Institutes of Science Education and Research (IISERs), students enrolled in certain programs, particularly the Ph.D. program, are typically eligible for fellowships. These fellowships are often funded by the government or specific research grants and are provided to support living expenses during the duration of the program.\n\nFor undergraduate students enrolled in the BS-MS dual degree program or other undergraduate initiatives, fellowships may not be automatically provided. However, students may have opportunities to apply for scholarships or financial aid based on merit or need.\n\nIt's important to check the specific details on the official IISER website or contact the institute directly for the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding fellowships available to students in different programs.",
